message: /* Extremely Sorry for the mistakes */ new section
If you've problem with the specific user, talk in their talk page. Not in the article talk.
It's the English version of கவுண்டர் page which backed by reliable sources.
There's no relativity between gounder title and vanniyar. For the confirmation, read the vanniyar page. They have "Padayachi or palli" as their title.
Refs and citations added according to wikipedia policy.
There's no need to remove notable people section. It sourced by wikipedia pages.
Citations needed for removed lines. It's just updated with proof of gowda which supports strong foundation to the page.

There are many images for this page! But some are hurts their feelings and emotions. So please respect their feelings while you upload some of the images. Or we'll file legal complaint to this page editor and wikipedia's organization.

Undid revision 1104100798 by [[Special:Contributions/Dr.Pinsky|Dr.Pinsky]] ([[User talk:Dr.Pinsky|talk]])  It's not your personal site to add your POV. All info should be neutralized without editorial bias. The consensus was finalized over there. It was agreed by the admin too. If you've a problem with the content, modify it instead of removing unnecessarily.
/* Varna Classification */ Added neutralized information and resource after finalizing consensus to prevent edit war and biased edits.

/* Social status */  Biased and the source is backed by edgar thurston. Many sources were marking vellalars were kshatriyas (yadu descent), vaishyas and sat-sudras. To prevent edit wars and biased vandalism, All sources should be included into the main page if you add varna classification.

Britannica isn't a valid ref. Britannica copies wikipedia. Many refs mentions he was vaishya, but someone insisted the term "shudra" without any valid refs and sources. It's wikipedia, not for a personal agenda. Three varna system only are in south india and it was known as brahmin, non-brahmin and dalits. Shudras were not allowed to study veda and wear sacred thread. But he worn the sacred thread. So, POV and personal agenda should be avoided here.
